This paper is primarily focused on the security and robustness of Deep Reinforcement Learning (Deep RL) algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the vulnerability of Deep Neural Networks (DNN) to adversarial attacks, which falls under the category of computer security, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses the application of RL agents in cyber-physical systems, which falls under the category of robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) possible sub-categories.
